# Binary treatment for precompute outputs: these files are large single-line
# JSON blobs (match_data.json can be 15-25MB, agent_trace.json 50KB-1MB). Without
# the -diff flag, GitHub PR views freeze trying to render a diff, and git merge
# attempts a textual three-way merge which is useless on these files.
#
# Related GOTCHAs:
#   GOTCHA-026 — Next.js Server-Component JSON Hydration Death
#   GOTCHA-027 — Trace Payload Explosion

# Static match payloads served to the dashboard
dashboard/public/match_data/*.json -diff linguist-generated=true
dashboard/public/match_data/*.duckdb binary

# DuckDB artifacts (if checked in)
*.duckdb binary

# YOLO weights / checkpoints (treat as binary)
*.pt binary
*.onnx binary
*.pth binary

# Video assets
*.mp4 binary
*.webm binary
*.mov binary

# Python bytecode (should be gitignored, but belt-and-suspenders)
*.pyc binary

# Bun/Node lockfiles — diff-friendly but huge; mark as generated so PR reviewers know
bun.lockb binary
bun.lock -diff linguist-generated=true
package-lock.json -diff linguist-generated=true
